pital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, Walailak University|School of Medicine]], [[Walailak University]]\n|\n|[[Nakhon Si Thammarat Province|Nakhon Si Thammarat]]\n|-\n|[[University of Phayao Medical Center and Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, University of Phayao|School of Medicine]], [[University of Phayao]]\n|\n|[[Phayao Province|Phayao]]\n|-\n|[[Phra Nang Klao Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, Siam University|School of Medicine]], [[Siam University]]\n|\n|Nonthaburi\n|-\n|[[Mae Fah Luang University Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, Mae Fah Luang University|School of Medicine]], [[Mae Fah Luang University]]\n|\n|[[Chiang Rai Province|Chiang Rai]]\n|-\n|[[Chulabhorn Hospital (Bangkok)]]\n|HRH Princess Chulabhorn College of Medical Science\n|\n|Bangkok\n|-\n|[[Sirindhorn Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, King Mongkut's Institute of Technology Ladkrabang|Faculty of Medicine]], [[King Mongkut's Institute of Technology Ladkrabang]]\n|[[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration#Medical Services Department|Medical Services Department]], [[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration]]\n|Bangkok\n|-\n|[[Lat Krabang Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, King Mongkut's Institute of Technology Ladkrabang|Faculty of Medicine]], [[King Mongkut's Institute of Technology Ladkrabang]]\n|[[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration#Medical Services Department|Medical Services Department]], [[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration]]\n|Bangkok\n|}\n[[File:Siriraj Hospital,Bangkok.jpg|thumb|[[Siriraj Hospital]], a university hospital]]\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Non-teaching University Hospitals in Thailand\n!Hospital Name\n!Affiliated University\n!Province\n|-\n|[[Siriraj Piyamaharajkarun Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine Siriraj Hospital, Mahidol University|Faculty of Medicine Siriraj Hospital,]] [[Mahidol University]]\n|Bangkok\n|-\n|[[Golden Jubilee Medical Center]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine Siriraj Hospital, Mahidol University|Faculty of Medicine Siriraj Hospital,]] [[Mahidol University]]\n|[[Nakhon Pathom Province|Nakhon Pathom]]\n|-\n|[[Hospital for Tropical Diseases (Thailand)|Hospital for Tropical Diseases]]\n|[[Faculty of Tropical Medicine, Mahidol University|Faculty of Tropical Medicine]], [[Mahidol University]]\n|[[Bangkok]]\n|-\n|[[Suan Sunandha Hospital]]\n|[[College of Allied Health Sciences and College of Nursing and Health, Suan Sunandha Rajabhat University|College of Allied Health Sciences and College of Nursing and Health]], [[Suan Sunandha Rajabhat University|Suan Sunandha Rajabhat University (Samut Songkhram Campus)]]\n|[[Samut Songkhram Province|Samut Songkhram]]\n|}\n[[File:KingChulalongkornMemorialHospital FirstBuilding and BhumisiriMangkhalanusornBuilding in October 2017.jpg|thumb|[[King Chulalongkorn Memorial Hospital]], a university hospital]]\n\n=== CPIRD Medical Education Centers ===\n[[File:\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e04\u0e32\u0e23\u0e28\u0e39\u0e19\u0e22\u0e4c\u0e41\u0e1e\u0e17\u0e22\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e36\u0e01\u0e29\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e31\u0e49\u0e19\u0e04\u0e25\u0e34\u0e19\u0e34\u0e04 \u0e23\u0e1e.\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e40\u0e14\u0e47\u0e08\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e15\u0e32\u0e01\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e19\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a.jpg|thumb|CPIRD Medical Education Center, [[Somdejphrajaotaksin Maharaj Hospital]], [[Tak Province]]]]\n\nIn 1994, the cabinet approved of a cooperation between the MOPH and Thai universities to organise a program known as the '''<nowiki/>'Collaborative Project to Increase Production of Rural Doctors (CPIRD)'''' in order to increase the number of medical personnel in rural areas of Thailand. To reach these goals, the cabinet set up the CPIRD Office in 1997 to oversee the project's activities. In terms of education, the preclinic level of study (years 1-3) will take place at the student's university or college. At the clinical level of study (years 4-6), study will take place at hospitals all around the country under the guidance of the MOPH. 'Medical Education Centers' ({{Lang-th|\u0e28\u0e39\u0e19\u0e22\u0e4c\u0e41\u0e1e\u0e17\u0e22\u0e28\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23\u0e28\u0e36\u0e01\u0e29\u0e32 \u0e0a\u0e31\u0e49\u0e19\u0e04\u0e25\u0e34\u0e19\u0e34\u0e01}}) have been established for medical students in the CPIRD program at these hospitals. There are currently 45 CPIRD Medical Education Centers in Thailand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cpird.in.th/|title=CPIRD}}</ref>\n'''<nowiki/>'''\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Hospitals with CPIRD Medical Education Centers in Thailand\n!Hospital name\n!Affiliated university\n!Affiliated institution (if present)\n!Province\n|-\n|[[Khon Kaen Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Khon Kaen University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Khon Kaen University]]\n|\n|[[Khon Kaen Province|Khon Kaen]]\n|-\n|[[Sunpasithiprasong Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Khon Kaen University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Khon Kaen University]]\n[[College of Medicine and Public Health, Ubon Ratchathani University|College of Medicine and Public Health]], [[Ubon Ratchathani University]]\n|\n|[[Ubon Ratchathani Province|Ubon Ratchathani]]\n|-\n|[[Maha Sarakham Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Khon Kaen University\n|\n|[[Maha Sarakham Province|Maha Sarakham]]\n|-\n|[[Udon Thani Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Khon Kaen University\n|\n|[[Udon Thani Province|Udon Thani]]\n|-\n|[[Prapokklao Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Chulalongkorn University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Chulalongkorn University]]\n|\n|[[Chanthaburi Province|Chanthaburi]]\n|-\n|[[Chonburi Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Chulalongkorn University\n|\n|[[Chonburi Province|Chonburi]]\n|-\n|[[Bhumibol Adulyadej Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Chulalongkorn University\n|[[Royal Thai Air Force#Directorate of Medical Services|Directorate of Medical Services]], [[Royal Thai Air Force|The Royal Thai Air Force]]\n|[[Bangkok]]\n|-\n|[[Chiangrai Prachanukroh Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Chiang Mai University]]\n|\n|[[Chiang Rai Province|Chiang Rai]]\n|-\n|[[Lampang Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University\n|\n|[[Lampang Province|Lampang]]\n|-\n|[[Saraburi Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine Thammasat University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Thammasat University]]\n|\n|[[Saraburi Province|Saraburi]]\n|-\n|[[Chumphon Khet Udomsak Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Thammasat University\n|\n|[[Chumphon Province|Chumphon]]\n|-\n|[[Surat Thani Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Thammasat University\n|\n|[[Surat Thani Province|Surat Thani]]\n|-\n|[[Buddhasothorn Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Thammasat University\n|\n|[[Chachoengsao Province|Chachoengsao]]\n|-\n|[[Songkhla Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Princess of Naradhiwas University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Princess of Naradhiwas University]]\n|\n|[[Songkhla Province|Songkhla]]\n|-\n|[[Phichit Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Naresuan University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Naresuan University]]\n|\n|[[Phichit Province|Phichit]]\n|-\n|[[Buddhachinaraj Phitsanulok Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Naresuan University\n|\n|[[Phitsanulok Province|Phitsanulok]]\n|-\n|[[Phrae Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Naresuan University\n|\n|[[Phrae Province|Phrae]]\n|-\n|[[Somdejphrajaotaksin Maharaj Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Naresuan University\n|\n|[[Tak Province|Tak]]\n|-\n|[[Uttaradit Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Naresuan University\n|\n|[[Uttaradit Province|Uttaradit]]\n|-\n|[[Chaophraya Abhaibhubejhr Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Burapha University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Burapha University]]\n|\n|[[Prachinburi Province|Prachinburi]]\n|-\n|[[Rayong Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Burapha University\n|\n|[[Rayong Province|Rayong]]\n|-\n|[[Queen Sirikit Naval Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Burapha University\n|[[Royal Thai Navy#Naval Medical Department|Naval Medical Department]], [[Royal Thai Navy|The Royal Thai Navy]]\n|[[Chonburi Province|Chonburi]]\n|-\n|[[Queen Savang Vadhana Memorial Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Burapha University\n|[[Thai Red Cross Society]]\n|[[Chonburi Province|Chonburi]]\n|-\n|[[Nakornping Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, University of Phayao|School of Medicine]], [[University of Phayao]]\n|\n|[[Chiang Mai Province|Chiang Mai]]\n|-\n|[[Phayao Hospital]]\n|School of Medicine, University of Phayao\n|\n|[[Phayao Province|Phayao]]\n|-\n|[[Maharat Nakhon Ratchasima Hospital]]\n|[[Praboromarajchanok Medicine Program, Mahidol University|Praboromarajchanok Institute]], [[Mahidol University]]\n|\n|[[Nakhon Ratchasima Province|Nakhon Ratchasima]]\n|-\n|[[Maharaj Nakhon Si Thammarat Hospital]]\n|Praboromarajchanok Institute, Mahidol University\n|\n|[[Nakhon Si Thammarat Province|Nakhon Si Thammarat]]\n|-\n|[[Sawanpracharak Hospital]]\n|Praboromarajchanok Institute, Mahidol University\n|\n|[[Nakhon Sawan Province|Nakhon Sawan]]\n|-\n|[[Ratchaburi Hospital]]\n|Praboromarajchanok Institute, Mahidol University\n|\n|[[Ratchaburi Province|Ratchaburi]]\n|-\n|[[Kalasin Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Mahasarakham University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Mahasarakham University]]\n|\n|[[Kalasin Province|Kalasin]]\n|-\n|[[Roi Et Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Mahasarakham University\n|\n|[[Roi Et Province|Roi Et]]\n|-\n|[[Srisangwon Sukhothai Hospital|Srisangworn Sukhothai Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, Mae Fah Luang University|School of Medicine]], [[Mae Fah Luang University]]\n|\n|[[Sukhothai Province|Sukhothai]]\n|-\n|[[Sukhothai Hospital]]\n|School of Medicine, Mae Fah Luang University\n|\n|[[Sukhothai Province|Sukhothai]]\n|-\n|[[Vachira Phuket Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, Walailak University|School of Medicine]], [[Walailak University]]\n|\n|[[Phuket Province|Phuket]]\n|-\n|[[Trang Hospital]]\n|[[School of Medicine, Walailak University|School of Medicine]], [[Walailak University]]\n[[Faculty of Medicine, Prince of Songkla University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Prince of Songkla University]]\n|\n|[[Trang Province|Trang]]\n|-\n|[[Hatyai Hospital]]\n|[[Faculty of Medicine, Prince of Songkla University|Faculty of Medicine]], [[Prince of Songkla University]]\n|\n|[[Songkhla Province|Songkhla]]\n|-\n|[[Yala Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Prince of Songkla University\n|\n|[[Yala Province|Yala]]\n|-\n|[[Naradhiwas Rajanagarindra Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Prince of Songkla University\n|\n|[[Narathiwat Province|Narathiwat]]\n|-\n|[[Pattani Hospital]]\n|Faculty of Medicine, Prince of Songkla University\n|\n|[[Pattani Province|Pattani]]\n|-\n|[[Surin Hospital]]\n|[[Institute of Medicine, Suranaree University of Technology|Institute of Medicine]], [[Suranaree University of Technology]]\n|\n|[[Surin Province|Surin]]\n|-\n|[[Buriram Hospital]]\n|Institute of Medicine, Suranaree University of Technology\n|\n|[[Buriram Province|Buriram]]\n|-\n|[[Chaiyaphum Hospital]]\n|Institute of Medicine, Suranaree University of Technology\n|\n|[[Chaiyaphum Province|Chaiyaphum]]\n|-\n|[[Sisaket Hospital]]\n|[[College of Medicine and Public Health, Ubon Ratchathani University|College of Medicine and Public Health]], [[Ubon Ratchathani University]]\n|\n|[[Sisaket Province|Sisaket]]\n|}\n\n== Private hospitals ==\nSome hospitals in Thailand are operated by the private sector by either a private limited company or a public limited company. Specialised private hospitals in the fields of [[ophthalmology]] and [[dentistry]] are common.\n\n[[File:Thailand Bangkok Bumrungrad International Hospital Campus.jpg|thumb|[[Bumrungrad International Hospital]], a private hospital]]\n\nThe term \"general hospital\", when referring to private hospitals, refer to hospitals which provide non-specialised care. Private hospitals with fewer than 30 beds are officially termed \"health centres\". Both accept patient admissions.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Health in Thailand]]\n* [[List of hospitals in Thailand]]\n* [[List of medical schools in Thailand]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n* This article incorporates material from the corresponding Thai article,